cell_ontology_term: medial ganglionic eminence derived GABAergic interneuron
internal globus pallidus core projecting neuron
rationale: Mapping to the general type GPi core (internal globus pallidus core projecting neuron) is based on location (soma in GPi, nested inside GPi shell neurons), prediced GABA neurotransmitter, Pvalb expression, and MapMyCells hierarchical annotation transfer mapping to primate GPi core (CS20250428_GROUP_0015).

Consistent with this cell set being composed of Pinealocytes, a combination of Pinealocyte markers Gngt1 and Crx can identify the cells in this cluster with a confidence (F-beta score) of 0.91 in the context of glutamatergic cells (Pinealocytes release glutamate) from the hippocampal formation dissection (which includes the pineal gland).
Mapping of this cell type is corroborated by MAPMYCELLS-based bioinformatic analysis of Osorno et al., 2022 and its spatial localization profile.
Mapping to tanycyte of subfornical organ based on spatial transcriptomics evidence.

Mapping of this cell set to the hypendemal cell type is supported by its location to the subcommisural organ (from spatial transcriptomics), its expression of Sspo and its general transcriptomic classification in a class (Astro-Epen) along with epdendymal cells, tanycytes and astrocytes.

cell_ontology_term: L5 extratelencephalic projecting glutamatergic cortical neuron

rationale: Mapping of this cell type is corroborated by spatial location, expression of Drd3, Drd1 and Gad1/2.
Mapping of this cell set to a SCN pacemaker neuron is supported by spatial transcriptomic evidence and specific expression of Avp, Nms, Vip and Cck.
Mapping of this cell set to a purkinje layer interneuron is supported by spatial location in the purkinje cell layer of the cerebellum
Mapping of this cell set to a cerebellar granule cell is supported by spatial location in the granule cell layer of the cerebellum
Mapping of this cell set to a oligodendrocyte precursor cell is supported by the expression of the markers Sox10 and Pdgfra
This maps to  GPin-BF Cholinergic GABA in the primate Basal Ganglion taxonomy, but is not restricted to the striatum in mice, rather it is more broadly expressed in various parts of the pallium.

cell_ontology_term: internal globus pallidus shell projection neuron
rationale: Mapped to the general type GPi shell neuron (internal globus pallidus shell projection neuron) based on soma location (to GPi & surrounding GPi core neurons), neurotransmitter (dual GABA-Glut), somastatin expression and MapMyCells heirarchical annotation transfer mapping to Primate GPi core (CS20250428_GROUP_0016) in the Basal Ganglion taxonomy.
Mapping of this cell type is supported by analysis: https://github.com/Cellular-Semantics/cellular_semantics_notebooks

Mapping of this cell set to a differentiation-committed oligodendrocyte is supported by spatial transcriptomic evidence and specific expression of Gpr17, Bmp4, Neu4, Fyn in the context of oligodendrocyte lineage cells.

Mapping of this cell set to a newly formed oligodendrocyte is supported by spatial transcriptomic evidence and specific expression of Tcf7l2, Klk6, Cemip2, Casr in the context of oligodendrocyte lineage cells.
Mapping of this cell set to a myelin-forming oligodendrocyte is supported by spatial transcriptomic evidence and specific expression of Ctps, Cldn11 in the context of oligodendrocyte lineage cells.
Mapping of this cell set to a mature myelinating oligodendrocyte is supported by spatial transcriptomic evidence and specific expression of Klk6 in the context of oligodendrocyte lineage cells.
